This paper focuses on the task of abstractive summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses neural networks for modeling and learning, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves ranking the importance of sentences, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses unsupervised learning, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE).
